<exercises xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="exer-consistency" ><title>Additional Practice</title>
<exercisegroup>
  <introduction>
  <p>
    In the following exercises, find the solution to the given linear system.
    If the system has infinite solutions,
    give <m>2</m> particular solutions.
  </p>
  </introduction>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc} 2x_1\amp +\amp 4x_2\amp =\amp 2\\ x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp =\amp 1 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1-2x_2</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1=1</m>,
        <m>x_2=0</m> and <m>x_1=-1</m>, <m>x_2=1</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc} -x_1\amp +\amp 5x_2\amp =\amp 3\\ 2x_1\amp -\amp 10x_2\amp =\amp -6 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=-3+5x_2</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1 = 3</m>,
        <m>x_2=0</m> and <m>x_1 = -8</m>, <m>x_2 = -1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc} x_1\amp +\amp x_2\amp =\amp 3\\ 2x_1\amp +\amp x_2\amp =\amp 4 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1</m>; <m>x_2=2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc} -3x_1\amp +\amp 7x_2\amp =\amp -7\\ 2x_1\amp -\amp 8x_2\amp =\amp 8 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=0</m>; <m>x_2=-1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc} 2x_1\amp +\amp 3x_2\amp =\amp 1\\ -2x_1\amp -\amp 3x_2\amp =\amp 1 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc} x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp =\amp 1\\ -x_1\amp -\amp 2x_2\amp =\amp 5 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccccc} -2x_1\amp +\amp 4x_2\amp +\amp 4x_3\amp =\amp 6\\ x_1\amp -\amp 3x_2\amp +\amp 2x_3\amp =\amp 1 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=-11+10x_3</m>; <m>x_2=-4+4x_3</m>; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1=-11</m>, <m>x_2 = -4</m>,
        <m>x_3=0</m> and <m>x_1 = -1</m>,
        <m>x_2 = 0</m> and <m>x_3 = 1</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccccc} -x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp +\amp 2x_3\amp =\amp 2\\ 2x_1\amp +\amp 5x_2\amp +\amp x_3\amp =\amp 2 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=-\frac23+\frac89x_3</m>;
        <m>x_2=\frac23-\frac59x_3</m>; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1 = -\frac23</m>, <m>x_2 = \frac23</m>,
        <m>x_3 = 0</m> and <m>x_1 = \frac49</m>,
        <m>x_2 = -\frac19</m>, <m>x_3 = 1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{rcl} -x_1-x_2+x_3+x_4\amp =\amp 0\\ -2x_1-2x_2+x_3\amp =\amp -1 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1-x_2-x_4</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free;
        <m>x_3=1-2x_4</m>; <m>x_4</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1 = 1</m>,
        <m>x_2 = 0</m>, <m>x_3 = 1</m>,
        <m>x_4 = 0</m> and <m>x_1 = -2</m>, <m>x_2 = 1</m>,
        <m>x_3 = -3</m>, <m>x_4=2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{rcl} x_1+x_2+6x_3+9x_4\amp =\amp 0\\ -x_1-x_3-2x_4\amp =\amp -3 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=3-x_3-2x_4</m>; <m>x_2=-3-5x_3-7x_4</m>;
        <m>x_3</m> is free; <m>x_4</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1 =3</m>,
        <m>x_2 = -3</m>, <m>x_3=0</m>,
        <m>x_4=0</m> and <m>x_1 = 0</m>,
        <m>x_2 = -5</m>, <m>x_3 =-1</m>, <m>x_4=1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccccc} 2x_1\amp +\amp x_2\amp +\amp 2x_3\amp =\amp 0\\ x_1\amp +\amp x_2\amp +\amp 3x_3\amp =\amp 1\\ 3x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp +\amp 5x_3\amp =\amp 3 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccccc} x_1\amp +\amp 3x_2\amp +\amp 3x_3\amp =\amp 1\\ 2x_1\amp -\amp x_2\amp +\amp 2x_3\amp =\amp -1\\ 4x_1\amp +\amp 5x_2\amp +\amp 8x_3\amp =\amp 2 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccccc} x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp +\amp 2x_3\amp =\amp 1\\ 2x_1\amp +\amp x_2\amp +\amp 3x_3\amp =\amp 1\\ 3x_1\amp +\amp 3x_2\amp +\amp 5x_3\amp =\amp 2 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=\frac13-\frac43x_3</m>;
        <m>x_2=\frac13-\frac13x_3</m>; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1 = \frac13</m>, <m>x_2=\frac13</m>,
        <m>x_3=0</m> and <m>x_1 = -1</m>,
        <m>x_2 = 0</m>, <m>x_3=1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccccc} 2x_1\amp +\amp 4x_2\amp +\amp 6x_3\amp =\amp 2\\ 1x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp +\amp 3x_3\amp =\amp 1\\ -3x_1\amp -\amp 6x_2\amp -\amp 9x_3\amp =\amp -3 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1-2x_2-3x_3</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Possible solutions: <m>x_1=1</m>, <m>x_2=0</m>,
        <m>x_3=0</m> and <m>x_1=8</m>,
        <m>x_2=1</m>, <m>x_3 = -3</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
 </exercisegroup>
 <exercisegroup>
  <introduction>
  <p>
    In the following exercises,
    state for which values of <m>k</m> the given system will have exactly <m>1</m> solution,
    infinite solutions, or no solution.
  </p>
  </introduction>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc}x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp =\amp 1\\2x_1\amp +\amp 4x_2\amp =\amp k \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Never exactly <m>1</m> solution; infinite solutions if <m>k=2</m>;
        no solution if <m>k\neq 2</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc}x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp =\amp 1\\x_1\amp +\amp kx_2\amp =\amp 1 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Exactly <m>1</m> solution if <m>k\neq 2</m>;
        infinite solutions if <m>k=2</m>; never no solution.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc}x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp =\amp 1\\x_1\amp +\amp kx_2\amp =\amp 2 \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Exactly <m>1</m> solution if <m>k\neq 2</m>;
        no solution if <m>k=2</m>;
        never infinite solutions.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\begin{array}{ccccc}x_1\amp +\amp 2x_2\amp =\amp 1\\x_1\amp +\amp 3x_2\amp =\amp k \end{array}</m>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Exactly <m>1</m> solution for all <m>k</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
 </exercisegroup>
    
</exercises>